      • createRDFTermFactory

        protected RDFTermFactory createRDFTermFactory()
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDFParserBuilder
        Create a new RDFTermFactory for a parse session.

        This is called by AbstractRDFParserBuilder.parse() to set AbstractRDFParserBuilder.rdfTermFactory(RDFTermFactory) if it is Optional.empty().

        As parsed blank nodes might be made with RDFTermFactory.createBlankNode(String), each call to this method SHOULD return a new RDFTermFactory instance.

        Overrides:
        createRDFTermFactory in class AbstractRDFParserBuilder<JenaRDFParserBuilder>
        Returns:
        A new RDFTermFactory

      • resetTarget

        protected void resetTarget()
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDFParserBuilder
        Reset all optional target* fields to Optional.empty()

        Note that the consumer set for AbstractRDFParserBuilder.getTarget() is NOT reset.

        Subclasses should override this and call super.resetTarget() if they need to reset any additional target* fields.

        Overrides:
        resetTarget in class AbstractRDFParserBuilder<JenaRDFParserBuilder>

      • parseSynchronusly

        protected void parseSynchronusly()
                          throws IOException
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDFParserBuilder
        Parse AbstractRDFParserBuilder.sourceInputStream, AbstractRDFParserBuilder.sourceFile or AbstractRDFParserBuilder.sourceIri.

        One of the source fields MUST be present, as checked by AbstractRDFParserBuilder.checkSource().

        AbstractRDFParserBuilder.checkBaseRequired() is called to verify if AbstractRDFParserBuilder.getBase() is required.

        Specified by:
        parseSynchronusly in class AbstractRDFParserBuilder<JenaRDFParserBuilder>
        Throws:
        IOException - If the source could not be read
